The paper focuses on zero-shot and few-shot learning, which are commonly studied in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) fields. The proposed method involves graph generation and relation modeling, which are also relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL) fields. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of a multi-head graph attention mechanism and GCN, which are commonly used in neural networks (cs.NE).
